1
00:00:06,810 --> 00:00:12,180
[Song: My Luck by Book Kasidet]

2
00:00:12,180 --> 00:00:15,550
♫ I must be the luckiest person ever ♫

3
00:00:15,550 --> 00:00:19,280
♫ My heart says you're the one to love ♫

4
00:00:19,280 --> 00:00:25,460
♫ With you it's wonderful. It's great for my heart ♫

5
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:28,960
♫ You turn an ordinary day ♫

6
00:00:28,960 --> 00:00:36,150
♫ Into something meaningful that I've never felt with anyone before ♫

7
00:00:36,150 --> 00:00:41,900
♫ I can't be without you now. I’m lucky to be with you ♫

8
00:00:50,400 --> 00:00:56,400
[Together, Cher and Gun | A Boss and A Babe]

9
00:00:57,700 --> 00:01:02,700
[Ai P'Jack]
(TN: P/Phi, refers to someone older)

10
00:01:14,540 --> 00:01:16,140
Hello, Ai P'Jack!

11
00:01:16,140 --> 00:01:18,840
Did you secretly change my ringtone?

12
00:01:18,840 --> 00:01:19,824
Yes, it was me.

13
00:01:19,824 --> 00:01:22,420
And you even set it to the max volume.

14
00:01:22,420 --> 00:01:24,580
Are you trying to wake up the neighbor, too?

15
00:01:24,580 --> 00:01:26,290
You sleep as if you're dead.

16
00:01:26,290 --> 00:01:30,230
You wouldn't wake up even if the neighbor kicked on your door.

17
00:01:30,233 --> 00:01:32,262
Go take a shower.

18
00:01:33,160 --> 00:01:34,670
What shower?

19
00:01:34,670 --> 00:01:38,330
I got ready before picking up your call, Phi.

20
00:01:38,330 --> 00:01:41,240
I woke up at 5 a.m. to iron my clothes.

21
00:01:41,240 --> 00:01:43,432
I'm locking my door now. See you out front.

22
00:01:43,432 --> 00:01:46,046
Call me when you arrive... Whoa!

23
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:50,460
No wonder I thought you sounded nearby.

24
00:01:50,460 --> 00:01:54,070
Wow. I didn't know you could teleport.

25
00:01:54,070 --> 00:01:56,460
When did you learn it?

26
00:01:57,180 --> 00:02:02,060
If I'd known, I would've only told Ai Zo where I kept my spare key.

27
00:02:02,060 --> 00:02:05,020
I shouldn't have told you, too.

28
00:02:05,020 --> 00:02:07,000
Go take a shower already!

29
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:09,960
You can't arrive later than your boss on your first day of your internship.

30
00:02:09,960 --> 00:02:12,320
You keep mentioning boss, boss, boss.

31
00:02:12,320 --> 00:02:16,646
I wonder how strict he can be.

32
00:02:33,660 --> 00:02:35,630
Dammit! Ai P'Jack!

33
00:02:35,630 --> 00:02:39,320
I know you're in a hurry, but stopping to let me put on my socks for half a minute,

34
00:02:39,320 --> 00:02:40,583
won't make the boss bite your head off.

35
00:02:40,583 --> 00:02:42,962
Shut up and walk quickly.

36
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:49,500
Hurry.

37
00:02:58,180 --> 00:03:00,120
Don't pick me up next time.

38
00:03:00,120 --> 00:03:03,320
Seeing you first thing in the morning wears me out before having to work.

39
00:03:03,320 --> 00:03:06,563
Today is the only day I'll pick you up. Hurry.

40
00:03:09,230 --> 00:03:10,830
Let's go!

41
00:03:14,048 --> 00:03:16,882
[Phenomenal Gaming]

42
00:03:41,040 --> 00:03:43,566
Hey. Go.

43
00:03:48,420 --> 00:03:51,600
Hello, I'm Cher.

44
00:03:51,600 --> 00:03:55,640
I watched your competition last week. It was great!

45
00:03:55,640 --> 00:03:59,860
I only knew Ai Jack at first. It's nice to know you, too.

46
00:03:59,860 --> 00:04:03,570
Let me tell you. The last competition was cutthroat.

47
00:04:03,570 --> 00:04:07,204
Everyone tried to stop me when I decided to attack the tower alone.

48
00:04:07,204 --> 00:04:10,846
Did you see how it turned out? Without my signature move...

49
00:04:10,846 --> 00:04:12,400
Cher.

50
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:13,760
Don't you stop me, P'Jack.

51
00:04:13,760 --> 00:04:15,960
- Phi—
- Hey, Jae!
(TN: Jae refers to an older woman of Chinese descent)

52
00:04:15,960 --> 00:04:18,206
You're looking for a coffee boy, right?

53
00:04:18,206 --> 00:04:20,666
Let Ai Cher do it.

54
00:04:20,666 --> 00:04:22,573
Then I'll leave it to you, Nong Cher.
(TN: Nong, refers to someone younger)

55
00:04:22,573 --> 00:04:27,320
We'd like two iced lattes, two hot americanos,

56
00:04:27,320 --> 00:04:30,796
and the last one, an extra-iced white mocha,

57
00:04:30,796 --> 00:04:35,400
with non-fat milk, no syrup, and no whipped cream.

58
00:04:36,500 --> 00:04:38,390
What was that last order again?

59
00:04:38,390 --> 00:04:39,680
Look at me say it.

60
00:04:39,680 --> 00:04:42,220
An extra-iced white mocha,

61
00:04:42,220 --> 00:04:46,600
non-fat milk, no syrup, and no whipped cream.

62
00:04:48,310 --> 00:04:50,100
Pardon? Whipped what?

63
00:04:50,100 --> 00:04:54,300
Are you sure that's coffee? Not some kind of magical spell.

64
00:04:54,300 --> 00:04:57,590
That's for the boss. Do not make any mistakes.

65
00:04:57,590 --> 00:05:00,400
Otherwise, he won't be able to drink it.

66
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:02,366
Wow.

67
00:05:02,366 --> 00:05:05,160
I'm wondering if he's ever ordered that himself.

68
00:05:05,160 --> 00:05:08,320
That's so long. He isn't considerate of those who order for him.

69
00:05:08,320 --> 00:05:11,763
Damn you, Cher! Stop complaining and hurry!

70
00:05:11,763 --> 00:05:15,056
Once you're done, bring them to the meeting room downstairs.

71
00:05:15,056 --> 00:05:17,953
And knock before you enter.

72
00:05:20,220 --> 00:05:21,790
Yes, Father.

73
00:05:21,790 --> 00:05:23,630
Keep that for me.

74
00:05:26,877 --> 00:05:28,050
Yes, Boss.

75
00:05:28,050 --> 00:05:31,840
Right away, Sir. Guys, meeting room.

76
00:05:31,840 --> 00:05:35,200
- It's that way!
- This way!

77
00:05:37,180 --> 00:05:39,320
No syrup...

78
00:05:40,054 --> 00:05:43,786
Americano and white mocha.

79
00:05:45,320 --> 00:05:48,125
Amer... Americano...

80
00:05:48,125 --> 00:05:49,523
Dammit!

81
00:05:49,523 --> 00:05:52,489
Americano and white mocha...

82
00:05:53,070 --> 00:05:55,406
With no what again?

83
00:05:56,790 --> 00:05:58,970
Non-fat milk.

84
00:05:58,970 --> 00:06:01,210
Right! Non-fat milk.

85
00:06:01,210 --> 00:06:05,300
What crazy person is so damn picky with coffee...

86
00:06:09,800 --> 00:06:12,766
Boss! Hello.

87
00:06:14,520 --> 00:06:17,220
You're so creative with your coffee.

88
00:06:17,220 --> 00:06:19,960
The barista must be very proud.

89
00:06:19,960 --> 00:06:23,973
I'm going to get your coffee before the café closes.

90
00:06:40,620 --> 00:06:43,528
What department is the new intern working for?

91
00:06:52,380 --> 00:06:54,593
So that's what I think, Boss.

92
00:07:01,690 --> 00:07:05,889
Three months. Is that how long it took you to think, Khun Jack?
(TN: Khun, is an honorific)

93
00:07:12,920 --> 00:07:15,040
Knock before entering.

94
00:07:20,620 --> 00:07:22,710
Knock, knock, knock!

95
00:07:24,090 --> 00:07:26,606
Your coffee is here!

96
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:31,640
Damn you, Laem. Why now?

97
00:07:34,310 --> 00:07:36,340
I could just go in, right?

98
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:42,859
Coffee is delivered.

99
00:07:48,430 --> 00:07:51,380
That's about it, Boss. That's briefly it.

100
00:07:51,380 --> 00:07:55,070
And why isn't it a survival horror game like I told you?

101
00:07:55,070 --> 00:07:59,493
Did you hear me wrong that day or were you not listening to what I told you?

102
00:08:00,080 --> 00:08:01,910
I heard you right, Boss.

103
00:08:01,910 --> 00:08:06,000
I just don't think survival horror is a good idea.

104
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:11,280
Yes, people love thrilling games, and that includes action-horror as well.

105
00:08:11,280 --> 00:08:14,340
But action-horror isn't as appealing as survival horror.

106
00:08:14,340 --> 00:08:19,640
Action-horror is appealing because players can fight against their enemies.

107
00:08:19,640 --> 00:08:23,660
The appeal you mention is preferential to an individual.

108
00:08:23,660 --> 00:08:27,550
To me, killing monsters to get to the next level is just plain—

109
00:08:27,550 --> 00:08:29,885
Why don't you add side missions then?

110
00:08:34,980 --> 00:08:38,170
Oh, I'm sorry.

111
00:08:38,170 --> 00:08:40,890
I apologize on his behalf. It's his first day of internship.

112
00:08:40,890 --> 00:08:42,890
He still has a lot to learn.

113
00:08:44,080 --> 00:08:47,840
Shut up and leave.

114
00:08:47,840 --> 00:08:49,230
What?

115
00:08:49,230 --> 00:08:52,110
Shut up and leave.

116
00:08:52,110 --> 00:08:53,940
What are you saying, P'Jack?

117
00:08:54,650 --> 00:08:56,260
You may leave now.

118
00:08:56,260 --> 00:08:59,120
Ah. I'm sorry again.

119
00:08:59,120 --> 00:09:00,820
Sorry.

120
00:09:02,290 --> 00:09:03,790
Wait.

121
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:11,700
Yes?

122
00:09:13,140 --> 00:09:14,346
What did you say just now?

123
00:09:14,346 --> 00:09:17,776
When exactly? I said a lot of things.

124
00:09:19,400 --> 00:09:23,020
Ah, side missions, right?

125
00:09:23,020 --> 00:09:25,480
It's his first day, Boss.

126
00:09:25,480 --> 00:09:28,175
- Let's—
- I'm not talking to you, Jack.

127
00:09:31,020 --> 00:09:35,093
I don't usually let interns voice their opinions,

128
00:09:35,093 --> 00:09:37,733
but I'll listen to yours today.

129
00:09:46,540 --> 00:09:48,140
Please.

130
00:09:49,250 --> 00:09:52,060
It's such an odd honor, Boss.

131
00:10:06,185 --> 00:10:08,167
Then...

132
00:10:08,167 --> 00:10:12,173
may I talk about the game genre first? Something is bothering me.

133
00:10:12,173 --> 00:10:13,253
Sure.

134
00:10:13,253 --> 00:10:16,830
I won't interrupt you until you raise your finger saying you're finished.

135
00:10:16,830 --> 00:10:18,430
Please.

136
00:10:20,810 --> 00:10:22,200
Okay.

137
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:23,750
Here's what I think, Boss.

138
00:10:23,750 --> 00:10:27,050
It's true that survival horror games are interesting,

139
00:10:27,050 --> 00:10:29,870
but not every game made is popular.

140
00:10:29,870 --> 00:10:35,230
In Thailand, only Home Sweet Home and ARAYA are successful.

141
00:10:35,230 --> 00:10:37,580
The rest stays unknown, Boss.

142
00:10:37,580 --> 00:10:41,370
It's not that people aren't making any games, it's just that they aren't successful.

143
00:10:41,370 --> 00:10:44,840
So I agree with P'Jack's idea.

144
00:10:44,840 --> 00:10:48,950
If Phenomenal Gaming tries making an action-horror game,

145
00:10:48,950 --> 00:10:53,740
we may be able to pull it off with side missions and other minor features.

146
00:10:53,740 --> 00:10:59,560
It could be a unique detail that distinguishes our company and becomes our signature.

147
00:11:04,860 --> 00:11:07,450
Oh, I forgot. I'm done.

148
00:11:19,090 --> 00:11:22,720
P'Jack, Ai Zo messaged me saying we're having BBQ pork this evening.

149
00:11:22,720 --> 00:11:24,230
Let's go, okay, Phi?

150
00:11:24,230 --> 00:11:26,360
P'Three and Hia Tub will be there.
(T/N: Hia, refers to an older man of Chinese descent)

151
00:11:26,360 --> 00:11:31,553
He said it was to celebrate my smooth first day of internship.

152
00:11:32,610 --> 00:11:35,520
Do you dare to call that a smooth first day, Ai Laem?

153
00:11:35,520 --> 00:11:40,546
Easy there, Older Brother. It's your little brother here.

154
00:11:41,860 --> 00:11:43,746
I don't know what the boss is on today.

155
00:11:43,746 --> 00:11:47,870
Normally if you interrupt him like that he would have told you off

156
00:11:47,870 --> 00:11:52,740
and informed your university that you have no manners.

157
00:11:52,740 --> 00:11:55,020
Then the university will be banned because of you.

158
00:11:55,020 --> 00:11:56,900
You're exaggerating.

159
00:11:56,900 --> 00:11:59,960
We all see that Boss isn't that mean.

160
00:11:59,960 --> 00:12:05,106
When I was speaking, he listened with no interruption.

161
00:12:06,500 --> 00:12:11,670
You are just bad-mouthing P'Gun. Do you realize that?

162
00:12:11,670 --> 00:12:16,066
Ai Laem, you better watch your mouth.

163
00:12:17,580 --> 00:12:19,584
You're pointing at my face again.

164
00:12:20,660 --> 00:12:23,966
But I've never seen our boss like that, either.

165
00:12:24,520 --> 00:12:27,573
He's never treated anyone else that way.

166
00:12:30,330 --> 00:12:34,783
Have I turned into the boss's favorite person on the first day of my internship?

167
00:12:34,783 --> 00:12:36,483
You...

168
00:12:39,230 --> 00:12:40,720
You ran out of stuff, right?

169
00:12:40,720 --> 00:12:42,440
There's only a computer screen left.

170
00:12:42,440 --> 00:12:44,900
You probably wouldn't hit me with the screen, right?

171
00:12:44,900 --> 00:12:46,580
Right. No more stuff.

172
00:12:46,580 --> 00:12:49,186
But my foot is left!

173
00:12:50,250 --> 00:12:51,750
Take them back.

174
00:12:52,560 --> 00:12:56,020
Yes, Boss. Right, Sir.

175
00:12:57,180 --> 00:12:58,880
Nong Cher.

176
00:13:00,180 --> 00:13:02,800
Boss wants to see you.

177
00:13:09,780 --> 00:13:12,460
You're so dead, Ai Laem.

178
00:13:20,790 --> 00:13:22,590
Excuse me.

179
00:13:48,110 --> 00:13:50,100
I'd like to get to know you.

180
00:13:50,860 --> 00:13:52,706
What?

181
00:13:54,490 --> 00:13:55,909
Why are you surprised?

182
00:13:55,909 --> 00:14:00,120
Is it weird if the boss wants to get to know his intern?

183
00:14:00,120 --> 00:14:04,460
No. I just thought you looked at my resume before you accepted me here.

184
00:14:04,460 --> 00:14:08,600
What is the HR for if I have to do that myself?

185
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:13,696
Well, isn't talking to me here more time-consuming than looking over my resume?

186
00:14:19,630 --> 00:14:21,430
I'm sorry.

187
00:14:23,830 --> 00:14:27,373
My name is Sarun. You can also call me Laem.

188
00:14:28,190 --> 00:14:29,810
So Laem is your nickname?

189
00:14:29,810 --> 00:14:32,490
But I heard Khun Aoi call you Cher.

190
00:14:32,490 --> 00:14:34,190
That's my nickname.

191
00:14:35,080 --> 00:14:37,760
Calm down, Boss. I'm not messing with you.

192
00:14:37,760 --> 00:14:41,210
Cher is my real nickname. Laem is the nickname friends gave me.

193
00:14:41,210 --> 00:14:44,753
My face is pointy, so they like to call me Laem (Pointy).

194
00:14:45,740 --> 00:14:50,160
Why did you ask me to call you Laem when your nickname is Cher?

195
00:14:50,160 --> 00:14:51,890
I like that name.

196
00:14:51,890 --> 00:14:55,160
It sounds natural. Don't you think?

197
00:15:12,970 --> 00:15:15,320
Is there something on my face?

198
00:15:25,540 --> 00:15:28,233
I finally found you.

199
00:15:29,626 --> 00:15:32,846
What? What did you say?

200
00:15:33,910 --> 00:15:36,840
I don't think we've met.

201
00:15:36,840 --> 00:15:38,960
Are you mistaking me for someone else?

202
00:15:42,060 --> 00:15:44,360
You did, didn't you?

203
00:15:51,150 --> 00:15:53,933
I finally found you.

204
00:15:55,420 --> 00:15:58,380
I don't think we've met.

205
00:15:58,380 --> 00:15:59,520
Are you mistaking me for someone else?

206
00:15:59,520 --> 00:16:02,550
No. I recognize you.

207
00:16:02,550 --> 00:16:04,750
You...

208
00:16:04,750 --> 00:16:06,772
It must be you.

209
00:16:07,960 --> 00:16:09,610
It's you.

210
00:16:09,610 --> 00:16:10,920
Definitely you.

211
00:16:10,920 --> 00:16:12,620
Boss.

212
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:17,600
Once you're done talking to yourself, please talk to me.

213
00:16:21,720 --> 00:16:23,120
Hold on.

214
00:16:23,960 --> 00:16:25,940
Don't tell me,

215
00:16:27,050 --> 00:16:29,370
are you my fan?

216
00:16:30,470 --> 00:16:32,600
That's not exactly it.

217
00:16:32,600 --> 00:16:35,433
But I can't fully deny it.

218
00:16:35,433 --> 00:16:38,373
I feel anxious when you're gone.

219
00:16:40,047 --> 00:16:42,000
I wasn't sure it was you at first.

220
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:44,110
But once I get to talk to you more, I'm confident—

221
00:16:44,110 --> 00:16:46,110
Damn!

222
00:16:48,160 --> 00:16:51,763
I didn't curse at you. I was just surprised.

223
00:16:52,780 --> 00:16:55,226
So you like watching game streams, too?

224
00:16:55,226 --> 00:16:59,250
Which livestream did you like or were you just impressed by my competitions?

225
00:16:59,250 --> 00:17:01,240
Games?

226
00:17:01,240 --> 00:17:04,350
Well, I know I'm good at playing games.

227
00:17:04,350 --> 00:17:07,100
Especially, when I compete. I look extra cool.

228
00:17:07,100 --> 00:17:12,347
I just didn't realize the CEO of Phenomenal Gaming was one of my fans.

229
00:17:12,347 --> 00:17:14,540
If I brag about this on my stream, people will go cra—

230
00:17:14,540 --> 00:17:16,705
Do you play games too?

231
00:17:16,705 --> 00:17:20,120
That's why you can develop Jack's opinion.

232
00:17:20,120 --> 00:17:22,263
If you didn't have any experience,

233
00:17:22,263 --> 00:17:25,049
you must have watched so many game movies.

234
00:17:25,049 --> 00:17:26,293
Are you remembering the wrong person?

235
00:17:26,293 --> 00:17:28,366
No. I'm definitely right.

236
00:17:28,366 --> 00:17:31,706
If I'm wrong, you must be someone who resembles him so much.

237
00:17:33,810 --> 00:17:35,580
It has to be you.

238
00:17:35,580 --> 00:17:37,183
I'm so lost here.

239
00:17:37,183 --> 00:17:40,703
Stop talking to yourself and talk to me, please.

240
00:18:40,280 --> 00:18:42,322
It's really you.

241
00:18:50,466 --> 00:18:52,266
So how is it? Tender, right?

242
00:18:52,980 --> 00:18:54,440
Hey, Laem.

243
00:18:54,440 --> 00:18:56,560
How was your first day of internship?

244
00:18:56,560 --> 00:18:59,580
My dear nong Zo, I don't want to brag.

245
00:18:59,580 --> 00:19:03,913
Even the fierce boss surrendered to me.

246
00:19:04,830 --> 00:19:07,240
Zo, you should ask Ai Jack instead.

247
00:19:07,240 --> 00:19:10,220
Do you think you'll get a decent answer from Ai Laem?

248
00:19:10,220 --> 00:19:11,803
I don't think so.

249
00:19:11,803 --> 00:19:13,696
Hey, Ai P'Three!

250
00:19:13,696 --> 00:19:15,740
I'm only speaking the truth!

251
00:19:15,740 --> 00:19:20,140
Over ten people in the meeting room had their eyes locked on me.

252
00:19:20,140 --> 00:19:22,573
They were all listening to me!

253
00:19:22,573 --> 00:19:26,213
There were only eight people in the room.

254
00:19:27,510 --> 00:19:29,610
Yes, whatever!

255
00:19:29,610 --> 00:19:35,150
What's important is that the boss listened to my opinion without interruptions.

256
00:19:35,150 --> 00:19:36,453
Is that true, P'Jack?

257
00:19:36,453 --> 00:19:39,423
Ai Zo, why did you ask that? Don't you believe me?

258
00:19:39,423 --> 00:19:42,320
- I do.
- What he said was somewhat true.

259
00:19:42,320 --> 00:19:44,760
The boss doesn't usually listen to anyone.

260
00:19:44,760 --> 00:19:47,380
Especially interns like him.

261
00:19:47,380 --> 00:19:51,120
Maybe he talked so much that the boss didn't get a chance to interrupt.

262
00:19:51,120 --> 00:19:53,290
- That's exactly what I thought.
- Right?

263
00:19:53,290 --> 00:19:54,930
Speaking of which,

264
00:19:54,930 --> 00:20:00,130
Ai Laem, you haven't told me why the boss asked to see you.

265
00:20:12,890 --> 00:20:14,873
It's really you.

266
00:20:16,120 --> 00:20:19,170
The owner of the channel, Die With My Food ASMR.

267
00:20:19,170 --> 00:20:20,770
Hey!

268
00:20:21,890 --> 00:20:24,180
Do you watch ASMR videos, too?

269
00:20:24,180 --> 00:20:28,220
Yes. I began watching them when I started having trouble sleeping.

270
00:20:28,220 --> 00:20:30,953
And I just so happen to like your channel the most.

271
00:20:31,850 --> 00:20:33,650
You're making me blush.

272
00:20:33,650 --> 00:20:35,460
I didn't think you'd recognize me.

273
00:20:35,460 --> 00:20:37,010
Can you believe

274
00:20:37,010 --> 00:20:41,080
I showed my videos to the people on my team once and they couldn't recognize me.

275
00:20:41,080 --> 00:20:44,414
By the way, where have you been? You haven't uploaded anything in a week.

276
00:20:44,414 --> 00:20:48,053
Ah, I went and got my wisdom tooth removed.

277
00:20:49,330 --> 00:20:51,026
Boss, how about this?

278
00:20:51,830 --> 00:20:56,926
If you like my voice, how about we talk more casually?

279
00:21:03,920 --> 00:21:06,870
I give an inch and you want a mile?

280
00:21:06,870 --> 00:21:09,420
Even though I like your voice very much,

281
00:21:09,420 --> 00:21:13,573
