282
00:21:14,780 --> 00:21:18,480
You can call me Laem. It might get us closer.

283
00:21:18,480 --> 00:21:20,000
No.

284
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:22,060
I'm calling you Cher.

285
00:21:24,100 --> 00:21:26,120
There's one more thing you should know.

286
00:21:26,120 --> 00:21:28,209
I don't like skinship.

287
00:21:28,209 --> 00:21:31,003
But you touched my face first.

288
00:21:35,920 --> 00:21:37,860
Whatever you say, Boss.

289
00:21:37,860 --> 00:21:41,576
Right. When will you upload the new video?

290
00:21:43,440 --> 00:21:46,830
If I can get it done, I'll probably upload it later tonight.

291
00:21:46,830 --> 00:21:49,710
By the time I finish my errands it'll be 9-10 p.m.

292
00:21:49,710 --> 00:21:53,000
Then I will edit the video until, like, 11 p.m.

293
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:54,700
Why?

294
00:22:05,780 --> 00:22:09,693
If it's so late, you don't have to upload the video.

295
00:22:10,720 --> 00:22:12,633
Why not?

296
00:22:15,680 --> 00:22:17,580
Because tonight,

297
00:22:18,410 --> 00:22:21,173
I'll call you and listen to your voice.

298
00:22:22,300 --> 00:22:24,100
What?

299
00:22:41,640 --> 00:22:43,300
Hey, Ai Laem!

300
00:22:43,300 --> 00:22:46,300
Wow! Have you been possessed?

301
00:22:46,300 --> 00:22:48,210
You've been quiet and still for a minute.

302
00:22:48,210 --> 00:22:50,380
Are you okay?

303
00:22:50,380 --> 00:22:52,606
Is he calling for real?

304
00:22:58,570 --> 00:23:00,420
Guys, I think I'm going to go.

305
00:23:00,420 --> 00:23:02,120
I forgot I had something to do.

306
00:23:02,120 --> 00:23:03,640
- Hey!
- Hey!

307
00:23:03,640 --> 00:23:05,666
Hold on, Ai Laem.

308
00:23:05,666 --> 00:23:08,300
You haven't answered my question.

309
00:23:08,300 --> 00:23:11,170
Or did Boss fire you? Is that why you don't want to tell?

310
00:23:11,170 --> 00:23:13,860
That would be too bad if he fired me.

311
00:23:13,860 --> 00:23:15,970
Let's put it this way.

312
00:23:15,970 --> 00:23:20,970
Your big boss is just my little fan.

313
00:23:20,970 --> 00:23:22,940
Hurry up and be nice to me.

314
00:23:22,940 --> 00:23:27,380
I'll be beneficial to your team in the future, Ai P'Jack!

315
00:23:27,380 --> 00:23:28,880
Ai Laem.

316
00:23:29,930 --> 00:23:31,620
What do you even mean?

317
00:23:31,620 --> 00:23:34,690
You guys don't have to know.

318
00:23:34,690 --> 00:23:35,883
I'm out of here.

319
00:23:35,883 --> 00:23:37,383
Hey.

320
00:23:37,980 --> 00:23:40,366
Are you going to tell us or not, Ai Laem?

321
00:23:41,260 --> 00:23:44,120
- I'm going to poke your eyes out.
- I'm doing the same to you.

322
00:23:44,120 --> 00:23:46,020
Fine. I give up.

323
00:24:00,660 --> 00:24:03,990
Oh, it's past 10 now.

324
00:24:13,220 --> 00:24:15,280
Are you going to call or what?

325
00:24:15,280 --> 00:24:18,213
Otherwise, I'll take a shower and go to bed.

326
00:24:59,440 --> 00:25:02,120
Hello, Khun Sarun. You have an unreceived parcel.

327
00:25:02,120 --> 00:25:04,900
- Please transfer your money...
- Damn it!

328
00:25:04,900 --> 00:25:09,180
It's almost 11, man. The post office is still open or what?

329
00:25:09,180 --> 00:25:12,540
Hey, why don't you try finding a new job?

330
00:25:12,540 --> 00:25:15,480
Aren't you afraid of karma for scamming people like this?

331
00:25:15,480 --> 00:25:20,980
I hope one day your family and relatives get scammed too and get all their money stolen.

332
00:25:20,980 --> 00:25:23,800
Then you will know how your victims feel.

333
00:25:23,800 --> 00:25:25,753
Goodnight, Phi!

334
00:25:54,900 --> 00:25:57,370
- Hello?
- Hi, Boss.

335
00:25:57,370 --> 00:26:01,580
It's my bad I didn't tell you the exact time you should call.

336
00:26:01,580 --> 00:26:03,500
But I'm so sleepy now.

337
00:26:03,500 --> 00:26:07,533
I'm afraid I'll fall asleep when you call. And you'll think I don't keep my word.

338
00:26:08,120 --> 00:26:10,020
I was just going to...

339
00:26:10,020 --> 00:26:12,680
What should I do to put you to sleep?

340
00:26:12,680 --> 00:26:16,500
Will it help if I keep talking? Or me chewing?

341
00:26:16,500 --> 00:26:20,640
But I just had BBQ pork, Boss. I'm really stuffed right now.

342
00:26:20,640 --> 00:26:24,233
It'd be too mean to make me eat again, Boss.

343
00:26:26,280 --> 00:26:29,340
Then I'll ask questions and you answer.

344
00:26:29,340 --> 00:26:31,200
Is there any limit?

345
00:26:31,200 --> 00:26:32,500
I'm so sleepy.

346
00:26:32,500 --> 00:26:36,587
Cher, If you're sleepy, you can go to sleep. I won't stop you.

347
00:26:36,587 --> 00:26:38,730
Hey, no way.

348
00:26:38,730 --> 00:26:43,226
What if I fall asleep and you have a hard time sleeping?

349
00:26:45,480 --> 00:26:50,280
Do you care that much about someone you've known for one day?

350
00:26:50,280 --> 00:26:52,840
Yes, I've known you for a day.

351
00:26:52,840 --> 00:26:56,026
But you've known me for a long time already, right?

352
00:27:05,350 --> 00:27:08,940
Oh, right. How did you get my number?

353
00:27:08,940 --> 00:27:10,390
I asked P'Aoi.

354
00:27:10,390 --> 00:27:14,720
Then I must speak to Khun Aoi and tell her that disclosing my number is punishable.

355
00:27:14,720 --> 00:27:17,490
Hey, Boss.

356
00:27:17,490 --> 00:27:19,980
Boss, please don't blame, P'Aoi.

357
00:27:19,980 --> 00:27:22,010
You know how I am.

358
00:27:22,010 --> 00:27:25,370
We kept talking until P'Aoi got carried away and gave me your phone number.

359
00:27:25,370 --> 00:27:28,920
If I didn't receive the nickname Ai Laem, there was another other for me.

360
00:27:28,920 --> 00:27:31,180
They say I talk until monkeys sleep.

361
00:27:32,890 --> 00:27:34,950
What are you laughing at?

362
00:27:34,950 --> 00:27:37,570
It's because I talk until monkeys sleep.

363
00:27:37,570 --> 00:27:40,986
That means, if I talk until monkeys sleep, that means you're a monkey.

364
00:27:48,150 --> 00:27:49,950
What's my name?

365
00:27:50,880 --> 00:27:54,260
Why do you ask? Or is it because you don't know what to ask?

366
00:27:54,260 --> 00:27:56,030
I want to test your knowledge.

367
00:27:56,030 --> 00:28:01,700
To see how much you know about my company before entering my company.

368
00:28:01,700 --> 00:28:03,180
Come on, Boss.

369
00:28:03,180 --> 00:28:07,640
Shouldn't a knowledge check be conducted during the interview stage?

370
00:28:07,640 --> 00:28:11,410
Your name is Gungawin.

371
00:28:11,410 --> 00:28:13,600
Anything else you want to ask?

372
00:28:13,600 --> 00:28:15,400
What am I like?

373
00:28:18,210 --> 00:28:20,780
From what I heard...

374
00:28:20,780 --> 00:28:23,360
you're a very harsh person.

375
00:28:23,360 --> 00:28:25,160
You don't listen to other people's opinions.

376
00:28:25,160 --> 00:28:28,606
And you seem like you don't have many friends.

377
00:28:29,840 --> 00:28:33,780
But I don't think you're that extreme. Right?

378
00:28:33,780 --> 00:28:36,780
Frankly speaking, I don't know.

379
00:28:36,780 --> 00:28:40,553
Ever since I was born, I've never been harsh on myself.

380
00:28:41,820 --> 00:28:44,570
Boss, let me tell you something.

381
00:28:44,570 --> 00:28:47,450
You don't have to be so strict.

382
00:28:47,450 --> 00:28:51,120
With your tie so tight to your neck every day, don't you feel uncomfortable?

383
00:28:51,120 --> 00:28:53,840
Allow your shirts to have wrinkles from time to time.

384
00:28:54,386 --> 00:28:58,453
And for your coffee, how about you drink something else sometimes?

385
00:28:59,340 --> 00:29:03,213
Why is that? Do you want me to step outside of the box?

386
00:29:03,213 --> 00:29:05,673
The coffee order is too long. I'm too lazy to remember it.

387
00:29:11,500 --> 00:29:12,933
I'm kidding.

388
00:29:12,933 --> 00:29:16,000
Yes, I want you to try stepping out of your comfort zone.

389
00:29:16,000 --> 00:29:22,370
I think creating games is like cooking.

390
00:29:22,370 --> 00:29:25,490
You add this and that for your clients.

391
00:29:25,490 --> 00:29:27,740
If you don't know your ingredients well,

392
00:29:27,740 --> 00:29:31,900
you wouldn't know which ingredients should be mixed, right?

393
00:29:31,906 --> 00:29:34,180
Something like that.

394
00:29:38,850 --> 00:29:41,410
Am I talking too much?

395
00:29:41,410 --> 00:29:44,240
People have warned me many times.

396
00:29:44,240 --> 00:29:47,140
I just can't help it.

397
00:29:47,140 --> 00:29:52,460
If I wasn't nicknamed "Laem" first, people might call me "foul-mouthed" instead.

398
00:29:53,370 --> 00:29:57,446
Let's just say I won't mind what you say tonight.

399
00:29:58,950 --> 00:30:00,640
I should have said it more savagely then.

400
00:30:00,640 --> 00:30:03,410
Hey. Are you asking for a mile after you get an inch?

401
00:30:03,410 --> 00:30:05,700
I'll take that as a compliment, Boss.

402
00:30:05,700 --> 00:30:08,620
You don't mind me. I don't mind you.

403
00:30:08,620 --> 00:30:10,420
We're even.

404
00:30:11,760 --> 00:30:13,700
You're just...

405
00:30:14,370 --> 00:30:17,760
I think he's sleepy now, Boss.

406
00:30:17,760 --> 00:30:19,873
I meant, Ai Laem.

407
00:30:22,660 --> 00:30:25,840
Cher? Cher?

408
00:30:41,210 --> 00:30:43,113
Goodnight, Cher.

409
00:31:28,520 --> 00:31:30,140
Did you get any sleep?

410
00:31:30,140 --> 00:31:31,380
I did.

411
00:31:31,380 --> 00:31:35,840
Believe it or not, since I started my internship up until now,

412
00:31:35,840 --> 00:31:38,370
I haven't played any games yet.

413
00:31:38,370 --> 00:31:39,780
That's good.

414
00:31:39,780 --> 00:31:43,020
What happened last night with the boss? Did he call?

415
00:31:43,020 --> 00:31:44,650
No.

416
00:31:44,650 --> 00:31:47,570
- Good.
- Because I called him.

417
00:31:47,570 --> 00:31:50,820
It's good he didn't call. Why did you call him?

418
00:31:50,820 --> 00:31:53,520
Well, I hate when things don't happen as scheduled.

419
00:31:53,520 --> 00:31:58,230
He said he'd call, so he has to. He said we'd talk, so we did.

420
00:31:58,230 --> 00:32:01,340
Ai Laem, please spare the boss.

421
00:32:01,340 --> 00:32:02,996
Don't get on his nerves.

422
00:32:02,996 --> 00:32:05,230
I'm not getting on his nerves.

423
00:32:05,230 --> 00:32:08,860
I'm trying to help your boss get a good night's sleep.

424
00:32:08,860 --> 00:32:14,006
Why do you always misinterpret my good intentions?

425
00:32:15,790 --> 00:32:19,250
Ai Laem! Fine. It's up to you then.

426
00:32:19,250 --> 00:32:22,666
But if you get fired before your internship is over,

427
00:32:22,666 --> 00:32:25,550
I'll just say you deserve it.

428
00:32:25,550 --> 00:32:27,510
Ai Laem!

429
00:32:27,510 --> 00:32:29,480
Hop on.

430
00:32:29,480 --> 00:32:31,639
You always look for trouble.

431
00:32:32,790 --> 00:32:35,106
Ai Laem, will you be more precise?

432
00:32:36,370 --> 00:32:38,780
If you're nagging so much, why don't you do it yourself?

433
00:32:38,780 --> 00:32:42,760
Kids, it's lunchtime. How about we have papaya salad today?

434
00:32:42,760 --> 00:32:46,470
Oh, I'd love to take you to Jae Phon's restaurant.

435
00:32:46,470 --> 00:32:47,820
It's the best papaya ever!

436
00:32:47,820 --> 00:32:49,465
Really? Where's that?

437
00:32:49,465 --> 00:32:51,520
- Udon Thani.
- Damn you!

438
00:32:51,520 --> 00:32:53,320
It's his mom's shop, Jae.

439
00:32:53,320 --> 00:32:55,860
Phon is his mother's name.

440
00:32:55,860 --> 00:32:59,966
Ah! Your mother's name is Phon.

441
00:33:01,290 --> 00:33:02,600
Come on, Jae!

442
00:33:02,600 --> 00:33:05,820
We stopped making fun of other people's parents' names long ago.

443
00:33:05,820 --> 00:33:08,040
Do people still do it these days?

444
00:33:08,040 --> 00:33:10,160
Oh, I forgot.

445
00:33:10,160 --> 00:33:12,396
You're from the old days.

446
00:33:14,340 --> 00:33:16,120
You'll get what's coming!

447
00:33:16,120 --> 00:33:19,270
Are we going or not? Come on. Chop-chop.

448
00:33:19,270 --> 00:33:22,020
- Jae, you've said it, alright.
- Free food...

449
00:33:22,020 --> 00:33:25,180
Oops! Why are we stopping?

450
00:33:26,520 --> 00:33:28,020
Boss.

451
00:33:28,730 --> 00:33:31,054
Why are you late for work today?

452
00:33:31,647 --> 00:33:35,300
I stopped by the hotel to check on something. Why?

453
00:33:35,300 --> 00:33:38,489
Nothing. I was just asking because you're late.

454
00:33:40,520 --> 00:33:41,653
Boss?

455
00:33:41,653 --> 00:33:43,750
Ai Laem!

456
00:33:43,750 --> 00:33:45,660
Will you stop talking?

457
00:33:45,660 --> 00:33:48,730
Your mom should've shut your mouth with coal as a kid.

458
00:33:48,730 --> 00:33:51,386
Why are you nagging, Ai P'Jack?

459
00:33:57,080 --> 00:33:59,080
What's the matter?

460
00:33:59,080 --> 00:34:00,520
Ah, nothing.

461
00:34:00,520 --> 00:34:02,720
We're going out for papaya salad.

462
00:34:02,720 --> 00:34:05,300
Would you like to join—

463
00:34:05,300 --> 00:34:06,905
Ow! I just got bitten by an ant.

464
00:34:06,905 --> 00:34:08,537
You pinched the wrong person!

465
00:34:09,680 --> 00:34:10,820
Ai Laem!

466
00:34:10,820 --> 00:34:12,160
No, thanks.

467
00:34:12,160 --> 00:34:14,654
But please get a coffee for me on the way back. My regular.

468
00:34:14,654 --> 00:34:16,466
What do you mean, regular?

469
00:34:16,466 --> 00:34:19,773
I'll get you something new. It'll surely be good!

470
00:34:22,490 --> 00:34:24,050
For sure!

471
00:34:24,050 --> 00:34:26,740
Please excuse us now, Boss.

472
00:34:31,120 --> 00:34:33,173
Oops. Wrong way.

473
00:34:34,450 --> 00:34:35,640
Let's go, hurry!

474
00:34:35,640 --> 00:34:37,720
What's wrong with you guys?

475
00:34:37,720 --> 00:34:39,970
- Don't say that!
- Ai Laem! How can you say that?

476
00:34:39,970 --> 00:34:41,367
- You can't say it like that.
- But he came late, though.

477
00:34:41,367 --> 00:34:43,966
You can't!

478
00:34:46,320 --> 00:34:48,952
- Just a moment, please.
- Sure.

479
00:34:52,160 --> 00:34:54,093
Nong Cher.

480
00:34:54,700 --> 00:34:56,160
Yes?

481
00:34:56,160 --> 00:34:59,640
It's better to be careful, dear.

482
00:35:01,280 --> 00:35:03,226
Uh... careful for what?

483
00:35:04,260 --> 00:35:07,250
Well, we can't say much.

484
00:35:07,250 --> 00:35:09,590
Can you spill it just a little then?

485
00:35:10,620 --> 00:35:13,140
Let's just say don't get too close to the boss.

486
00:35:13,140 --> 00:35:16,430
Especially alone together. Don't!

487
00:35:17,700 --> 00:35:21,120
You're saying it like he's a serial killer or something.

488
00:35:21,120 --> 00:35:24,320
Although he's not,

489
00:35:24,320 --> 00:35:26,640
we can't say much.

490
00:35:26,640 --> 00:35:29,333
We're warning you because we mean well.

491
00:35:29,333 --> 00:35:34,603
You're slender framed and look mixed. Be careful of...

492
00:35:35,490 --> 00:35:37,740
You know...

493
00:35:37,740 --> 00:35:42,670
Thank you so much for your concern.

494
00:35:42,670 --> 00:35:43,914
What era is this already?

495
00:35:43,914 --> 00:35:46,680
Who eats who or who gets eaten is their choice to make.
(TN: He's talking about sexual orientation)

496
00:35:46,680 --> 00:35:49,960
For example, you can choose what you want to eat at your lunchtime.

497
00:35:49,960 --> 00:35:52,020
Right?

498
00:35:52,020 --> 00:35:53,520
Yes.

499
00:35:55,070 --> 00:35:56,839
Your coffee is ready.

500
00:35:57,710 --> 00:35:59,320
Thank you.

501
00:35:59,320 --> 00:36:01,945
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

502
00:36:09,330 --> 00:36:10,420
What would you like to order?

503
00:36:10,420 --> 00:36:13,300
An extra-iced white mocha, with non-fat milk, and no syrup.

504
00:36:13,300 --> 00:36:15,546
I got you whipped cream today.

505
00:36:16,350 --> 00:36:18,293
You didn't knock.

506
00:36:21,380 --> 00:36:23,080
I just did.

507
00:36:24,140 --> 00:36:26,170
I got you tuna sandwiches too.

508
00:36:26,170 --> 00:36:30,200
P'Aoi said it's the only type of sandwich you eat. Right?

509
00:36:30,200 --> 00:36:31,900
Right.

510
00:36:33,820 --> 00:36:35,410
But I didn't order it.

511
00:36:35,410 --> 00:36:37,632
And I don't eat whipped cream either.

512
00:36:38,640 --> 00:36:40,280
Come on, Boss.

513
00:36:40,280 --> 00:36:43,860
We talked about this last night. About stepping outside of your comfort zone.

514
00:36:43,860 --> 00:36:46,320
I was so sleepy, yet I remember it.

515
00:36:46,320 --> 00:36:47,960
Don't you remember?

